                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9411/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-17T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 17, 1941―7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>234. Your 552, April 14, 6 p.m., numbered paragraph 1. The Department notes the
                    statement that the documents published in Tokyo relating to the pact of
                    neutrality concluded between the Soviet Union and Japan are represented to be
                    merely summaries of the treaty and of the accompanying joint declaration. What
                    has been reported from Moscow as the text of the pact and of the accompanying
                    joint declaration published there does not differ materially from the summaries
                    reported by you. The Department would appreciate your comments as to whether the
                    designation by the Japanese Government of the pact and the accompanying
                    declaration as summaries has any special significance.<note n="72"
                        xml:id="d787fn72">The Ambassador in Japan, in telegram No. 579, April 19, 11
                        a.m., replied that the designation had “no special significance and is
                        merely a device to avoid a breach of the law which forbids the publication
                        of the text of treaties prior to their ratification by the Emperor and
                        publication in the <hi rend="italic">Official Gazette</hi>.”
                        (761.9411/110)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
